    public static class HFile.FileInfo
extends Object
implements SortedMap<byte[],byte[]>
    Metadata for this file. Conjured by the writer. Read in by the reader.

      • append

        public HFile.FileInfo append(byte[] k,
                             byte[] v,
                             boolean checkPrefix)
                      throws IOException
        Append the given key/value pair to the file info, optionally checking the key prefix.
        参数:
        k - key to add
        v - value to add
        checkPrefix - whether to check that the provided key does not start with the reserved prefix
        返回:
        this file info object
        抛出:
        IOException - if the key or value is invalid

      • parseWritable

        void parseWritable(DataInputStream in)
            throws IOException
        Now parse the old Writable format. It was a list of Map entries. Each map entry was a key and a value of a byte []. The old map format had a byte before each entry that held a code which was short for the key or value type. We know it was a byte [] so in below we just read and dump it.
        抛出:
        IOException
